---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="EGGlang Documentation">
  <section class="documentation-section">
    <h1>EGGlang Documentation</h1>
    <p>
      Learn about EGGlang syntax, built-in functions, and programming paradigms.
    </p>

    <div class="documentation-content">
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <p>
        EGGlang is a simple programming language designed for learning and
        experimentation. Here's how to get started:
      </p>
      <pre><code>
do(
    define(x, 10),
    define(y, 20),
    define(sum, +(x, y)),
    print(sum)
)
      </code></pre>

      <h2>Built-in Functions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>print(value)</code>: Prints the value to the output.</li>
        <li><code>+(a, b)</code>: Adds two numbers.</li>
        <li><code>-(a, b)</code>: Subtracts two numbers.</li>
        <li><code>*(a, b)</code>: Multiplies two numbers.</li>
        <li><code>/(a, b)</code>: Divides two numbers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Control Structures</h2>
      <p>EGGlang supports the following control structures:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <code>if(condition, then, else)</code>: Executes <code>then</code> if the
          condition is true, otherwise executes <code>else</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>while(condition, body)</code>: Repeats the body while the
          condition is true.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>do(...)</code>: Executes multiple expressions in sequence.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .documentation-section {
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .documentation-content {
    text-align: left;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .documentation-content h2 {
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .documentation-content p {
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .documentation-content pre {
    background-color: #f5f5f5;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .documentation-content ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    color: #666;
  }

  .documentation-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
